message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.NEURON - The paper proposes a deep learning approach for statistical shape modeling from raw images, which involves using a convolutional neural network (CNN) to extract a low-dimensional shape representation directly from 3D images. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the paper applies the proposed method to medical imaging data for three different applications, which suggests relevance to the medical imaging (cs.MED) category. The use of a neural network also suggests relevance to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. Finally, the paper involves the use of a novel data augmentation procedure and leverages limited training data, which suggests relevance to the neural networks and deep learning (cs.NEURON) category.
